name: Rogoe
content:
Boss Rogoe was a rogue Gungan warlord who resided in the ancient fortress city Spearhead on the planet Naboo. Millennia before the Imperial Era, Rogoe became one of the last holdouts against Boss Gallo, a warlord who had united the warring Gungan tribes. Gallo destroyed Spearhead and laid the foundations of a new Gungan capital, Otoh Gunga.
Rogoe was mentioned in the new Star Wars canon in Nexus of Power, a 2016 Fantasy Flight Games sourcebook for the Star Wars: Force and Destiny roleplaying game. In the Star Wars Legends continuity, Boss Rogoe was first mentioned in Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds: Prima's Official Strategy Guide by Steven L. Kent, released on November 7, 2001, before appearing in the LucasArts video game Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds, released on November 11 the same year.
